title: -Helium Production In Fe,Cr,Ni,Ti and Cu Due To The Fission Neutron Part of Reactor Spectra.-

x4freetext: LETTER BY WALLIN.

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Nuclear Cross-Sections Techn. Conf., Washington 1968, Vol.1, p.125 (1968)

x4freetext: PRELIMINARY RESULT FOR NI ONLY.
-HELIUM PRODUCTION IN FE,CR,NI,TI AND CU DUE TO THE
FISSION NEUTRON PART OF REACTOR SPECTRA.-
R2 REACTOR, MTR-TYPE.
FAST NEUTRON FLUX ABOUT 1.E+14 NEUTRONS/CM-SQ/SEC.
MASS SPECTROMETER.
IRRADIATIONS WERE PERFORMED IN THE R2
REACTOR.
.FAST NEUTRON FLUX.  DURING IRRADIATION, SPECIAL
PRECAUTIONS WERE TAKEN TO AVOID CONTRIBUTION FROM
THERMAL NEUTRONS.
THE PUREST MATERIALS COMMERCIALLY AVAILABLE.
.THE SAMPLE CONTAINERS WERE SURROUNDED BY BORAL SHIELDS
WITH SEVERAL HUNDRED MG/CM2 OF BORON.
.AS THE MONITORS FOR THE FAST NEUTRON DOSE,NI,TI AND CU
WERE USED.
.IRRADIATION OF 10 DAYS IN A FAST NEUTRON FLUX.
.THE AMOUNT OF HE-4 DETERMINED BY A MASS SPECTROMETRIC
TECHNIC.
GAMMA SPECTROMETER FOR MEASUREMENT OF THE
MONITOR ACTIVITY TO GIVE THE TOTAL NUMBER OF REACTIONS
OCCURING IN THE MONITOR DURING IRRADIATION.
.THE FISSION SPECTRUM AVERAGED CROSS SECTIONS ARE
DETERMINED FROM THE RATIO OF THE REACTION PROBABILITY.
.THE NORMALIZATION OF THE REACTOR FLUX IS BASED ON A
COMPARISON OF THE REACTOR AND FISSION SPECTRA ABOVE
6.0 MEV.
TABLE 2, PRIVATE COMMUNICATION FROM
WEITMAN, OCT. 1970.
.THE ONLY IMPORTANT CORRECTION FOR HELIUM PRODUCTION
WAS DUE TO 7-N IN 26-FE (10 PER-CENT), 8-O IN 24-CR
(30 PER-CENT) AND 8-O PLUS 7-N IN 22-TI (5 PER-CENT).
.OTHER IMPURITY CORRECTIONS ARE MUCH LESS SIGNIFICANT.
.A SMALL SPECTRAL CORRECTION WAS CONSIDERED.
NORMALIZATION ERROR IS NOT GIVEN.
